$interpreted: Theodore: Foolish being. I command you to release me at once.
Phantom: How many loyal servants had their names tarnished and left to rot in prison? How many brave generals were stripped of their dignity and died in vain?
Phantom: If it wasn't for our corpses paving the way for you, you would never be where you are today!
Theodore: If it wasn't for me, Kingdom of the Sun will never obtain its current prosperity! Their sacrifaces were part of their dedication to the kingdom!
Theodore: All I have done was for the purpose of serving a greater cause!
Phantom: LIES!
Phantom: The only purpose you have is to satisfy your greed for power! All because you are jealous! Jealous of your brother!

Theodore: William is too soft and weak.
He couldn't protect the Kingdom of the Sun!!!

Phantom: Then how about me?
Am I also another stepping stone on your path to immense power?
Jahan: Your Majesty, are you alright? Did you have a bad night of sleep?
Jahan: I have a family recipe for a medicine. It's very effective against sleeping disorders. How about his Majesty give...
Theodore: S... Stand down!
Theodore: What's the deal with Todd?

Jahan: Turns out his loyalty was all bogus; this man had the gall to attempt assassination on your Majesty.
Fortunately, Jahan was right there to stop him.
Theodore: Is that so?
Jahan: Yes, your Majesty.
Theodore: Hmm... how's everything going?

Jahan: All going according to plan. 
If your Majesty has no more requests, I shall take my leave.
Theodore: Hold it.
Jahan: Your Majesty, is there anything else you want?

Theodore: Those things you are doing now,
If they ever get my hands dirty...
Jahan: Absolutely not. Jahan is very careful with things. I will not cause your Majesty even the teeniest spec of trouble...
Theodore: Good... now leave.
